quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  26,64,"And We advanced thereto the others [i.e., the pursuers]."
  26,65,"And We saved Moses and those with him, all together."
  26,66,"Then We drowned the others."
  27,37,"Return to them, for we will surely come to them with soldiers that they will be powerless to encounter, and we will surely expel them therefrom in humiliation, and they will be debased."
  27,38,"[Solomon] said, "
  27,39,"A powerful one from among the jinn said, "
  28,10,"And the heart of Moses' mother became empty [of all else]. She was about to disclose [the matter concerning] him had We not bound fast her heart that she would be of the believers."
  28,11,"And she said to his sister, "
  28,12,"And We had prevented from him [all] wet nurses before,{1} so she said, ",1:[Prior to that, Moses had refused to nurse from any other woman.]
